183
00:09:05.505 --> 00:09:07.845
The N-Z-S-I-S is intensifying efforts

184
00:09:07.865 --> 00:09:11.885
to promote a stronger security mindset across a board range

185
00:09:11.905 --> 00:09:14.925
of sectors in our society, including

186
00:09:14.925 --> 00:09:17.405
through our annual security threat environment report,

187
00:09:18.985 --> 00:09:21.405
new Zealand's relationships, our innovation,

188
00:09:22.065 --> 00:09:23.685
our location in the South Pacific

189
00:09:24.065 --> 00:09:26.525
and our close proximity to Antarctica,

190
00:09:27.025 --> 00:09:30.965
all make New Zealand geo strategically significant.

191
00:09:32.445 --> 00:09:33.735
This has been positive

192
00:09:33.815 --> 00:09:35.775
for New Zealand's international reputation

193
00:09:36.115 --> 00:09:37.495
and our economic prosperity,

194
00:09:38.355 --> 00:09:41.535
but that geostrategic significance also brings

195
00:09:41.565 --> 00:09:44.575
with it some downstream threats to our national security.

196
00:09:45.645 --> 00:09:47.395
There continues to be a number of states

197
00:09:47.395 --> 00:09:49.195
that conduct foreign interference in

198
00:09:49.345 --> 00:09:50.595
espionage in New Zealand.

199
00:09:51.725 --> 00:09:53.495
This is not benign activity.

200
00:09:54.405 --> 00:09:58.455
Such actors have a voracious appetite for covert influence

201
00:09:58.875 --> 00:10:01.735
and non-public information that they can leverage

202
00:10:01.735 --> 00:10:04.855
to gain an advantage over us and our partners.

203
00:10:05.675 --> 00:10:08.975
For example, increasingly we see influential New Zealanders

204
00:10:09.155 --> 00:10:10.495
or people with access to

205
00:10:11.055 --> 00:10:13.095
privileged information being targeted

206
00:10:13.315 --> 00:10:14.735
by foreign intelligence services

207
00:10:14.805 --> 00:10:16.895
through deceptive online recruitment.

208
00:10:17.845 --> 00:10:20.095
Certain states also want us to line up

209
00:10:20.095 --> 00:10:22.535
with their talking points and ensure our communities

210
00:10:22.535 --> 00:10:25.175
and civil society don't speak out of turn.

211
00:10:26.105 --> 00:10:27.995
Deception, coercion

212
00:10:27.995 --> 00:10:30.275
and corruption are frequently used

213
00:10:30.575 --> 00:10:33.235
to further their goals in ways that are contrary

214
00:10:33.235 --> 00:10:34.275
to our national interest.

215
00:10:35.175 --> 00:10:37.235
The fact that we now have criminal offenses

216
00:10:37.255 --> 00:10:40.195
for such activities reinforces that foreign interference

217
00:10:40.195 --> 00:10:42.915
and espionage is unacceptable In New Zealand.

218
00:10:44.055 --> 00:10:45.555
The N-Z-S-I-S continues

219
00:10:45.555 --> 00:10:47.755
to have success disrupting foreign interference

220
00:10:47.815 --> 00:10:49.035
and espionage activity,

221
00:10:50.315 --> 00:10:52.735
but what we see may just be the tip of the iceberg.

222
00:10:54.085 --> 00:10:57.265
As always, prevention will be the best defense,

223
00:10:57.925 --> 00:10:59.745
and there is much that organizations

224
00:10:59.805 --> 00:11:01.865
and communities can do to manage the risk.

225
00:11:02.685 --> 00:11:04.465
We have some excellent advice and guidance,

226
00:11:05.005 --> 00:11:07.545
but leaders of organizations, businesses

227
00:11:07.645 --> 00:11:10.185
and communities also need to take steps

228
00:11:10.245 --> 00:11:11.305
to protect their people,

229
00:11:11.835 --> 00:11:13.945
their critical information and their assets.

